This paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for edge detection, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of Xception networks, which are a type of deep neural network architecture, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a large dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
